results.title: The Fountain of Goof (FOG) Tv Network Presents As the Butter Flies
results.description:
The Fountain of Goof (F.O.G.) Tv Network
Presents: A heartwarming short story/kodak moment called: 

As the Butter-Flies

Written by The Muse...Awesome City, Texas

Introduction:  Chicken Little’s sister, Thunderbird...a homing pigeon who wears nerdy looking reading glasses…(a v.i.p. of sorts - Very Important Pigeon) is a small, winged creature who can swiftly fly into healing action soon after seeing bolts of lightning flash from the sky...obviously, signal waves of approval from a land Har-Har away…    :)

It was an early autumn morning...Thunderbird sat quietly and patiently nestled within a tall, shady oak tree...eating leftover bread crumbs or whatever was tossed her whey.  Though, she appeared to be quiet and shy...some of her bold character derived from (smart) cookie crumbs that were uncaringly tossed behind from messy bird-brains.

Her long, feathered wings covered her small body with warmth, safety and care. She closed her eyes and waited for the next adventure to unfold.  

Most days were busy retrieving twigs and pieces of grass for her neighboring friends...as well as catching a grasshopper or two (crickets if she was “lucky”) to feed the younger ones...and herself.

She sat still...then...suddenly, she heard a bit of rustling nearby.  She slowly opened her eyes to see a small southern creature hiding/lurking behind a neighbor's tree.  It appeared to be tip toeing thru some tulips...and looked like one of the cast members from...Oh, what's that classic movie called?   Bah, Humbug Mr. Dickens...or something of that nature…

Tho, its feathers looked like second hand “wings” apparel (like most of us), signals from Har-Har away quickly informed Thunderbird otherwise.

When the bird-like creature walked closer, Thunderbird noticed that it had been hurt or injured of some sort.  Its eyes were big and round and greyish.  It didn't tweet or sing or even want to look anywhere but towards the ground. 

You’d think most winged animals are out and about happily searching for their usual finds or chasing after one another...or “hanging out” with the same usual feathered crowd. 

Thunderbird...being her usual thunderbird self, quietly flew down to ask whats-da-matter?

“Hey there birdie….what’s-da-matter?  “R-u-ok?” 

It couldn't respond....just stared into Thunderbird’s eyes.

“Ehh...Did you lose or forget something?  Or...did some doh-doh take anything of yours…?  “Hmm…?”

“After a brief moment, it answered, “Yes...I was about to have my morning breakfast...and...and...someone stole my parkay butter to put on my breakfast toast”...sniffling its little nose...as it covered its face with one wing.

“I don't know why...parkay…”Parkay”….?”  

Without hesitation, Thunderbird immediately flew to her place of dwelling and retrieved a small “stick" of butter and placed it near the creature…

“Here...I hope this’ll make you feel better” Thunderbird said softly.

It could only smile as she picked it up and flew to a nearby tree branch.

Thus, a happy ending to a butter-ball tale of a story...called:

As the Butter-Flies.  :)

Eggster Monsalve
The Muse from Awesome City, Texas
